text.section:
"Local government" means:
A chartered county established under Article 25A of the Code;
A code county established under Article 25B of the Code;
A board of county commissioners established or operating under Article 25 of the Code;
Baltimore City;
A municipal corporation established or operating under Article 23A of the Code;
The Maryland-National Capital Park and Planning Commission;
The Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission;
The Northeast Maryland Waste Disposal Authority;
A community college or board of trustees for a community college established or operating under Title 16 of the Education Article, not including Baltimore City Community College;
A county public library or board of trustees of a county public library established or operating under Title 23, Subtitle 4 of the Education Article;
The Enoch Pratt Free Library or Board of Trustees of the Enoch Pratt Free Library;
The Washington County Free Library or the Board of Trustees of the Washington County Free Library;
A special taxing district;
A nonprofit community service corporation incorporated under State law that is authorized to collect charges or assessments;
Housing authorities created under Division II of the Housing and Community Development Article;
A sanitary district, sanitary commission, metropolitan commission, or other sewer or water authority established or operating under public local law or public general law;
The Baltimore Metropolitan Council;
The Howard County Economic Development Authority;
The Howard County Mental Health Authority;
A commercial district management authority established by a county or municipal corporation if provided under local law;
The Baltimore City Police Department;
A regional library resource center or a cooperative library corporation established under Title 23, Subtitle 2 of the Education Article;
Lexington Market, Inc., in Baltimore City;
The Baltimore Public Markets Corporation, in Baltimore City;
The nonprofit corporation serving as the local public transportation authority for Carroll County pursuant to a contract or memorandum of understanding with Carroll County (Carroll County Senior Overland Service, Inc., t/a Carroll Area Transit System);
The nonprofit corporation serving as the animal control and licensing authority for Carroll County pursuant to a contract or memorandum of understanding with Carroll County (the Humane Society of Carroll County, Inc.);
Garrett County Municipalities, Inc., in Garrett County; and
The nonprofit corporation serving as the local public transportation authority for Garrett County pursuant to a contract or memorandum of understanding with Garrett County (Garrett County Community Action Committee, Inc.).
